caption: It's clear to me that this restaurant places little to no emphasis on the service aspect of the experience. There are so many points I could bring up about how it was lacking, but let's just say it took nearly 3 hours from start to finish. I could have walked out without paying without anyone noticing, but finally decided to walk up to the bar and ask for service myself. For the price, one would expect the service to be passable at least. Will not be returning.

Birthday lunch for my daughter-in-law.  We ordered takeout and they were very timely.  The order was ready right when they said it would be.  Dedicated parking on the street made it easy to get in and out.  Food was excellent as always.  My daughter-in-law eats vegetarian, and the Verisoy option was very tasty.

Ordered from door dash. Our egg rolls were amazing. Sushi was amazing. Only reason we down-scored was the spice level of my husband's order. Husband ordered drunken fried rice with 1/10 stars spice level. It was so spicy we literally had to throw it away. Inedible. We might have ordered 1/10 stars but whoever reads the orders just ignored it. It would have been less painful to just burn the $20 instead eating that spicy food. My husband didn't want to waste it so he kept trying to take bites (6/7 total) and now he is throwing up in the bathroom.
On Saturday night this was the only restaurant that would seat our table of four without a wait of 1 & 1/2 hours. The food and drinks were delicious and service was fast.
Best thai in Boise!

Walked in with my boys, bags of food orders lined the bar. No hostess, so we walked back towards the restaurant. Server sees us but doesn't greet us. Starts chatting with two guys she's serving. Restaurant is pretty empty  We wait, 5-6 minutes go by. Nobody comes, waitress still chatting. We left. Might be best food in the world but your service is horrible. Get good employees or find someone to greet people at least. Basic customer service seems lost anymore.
Horrible service. Extremely long wait times if you order online.
Sat in the back room and shared SO much food with friends. Everything we had from entrées to sushi rolls was amazing. Great service as well.

food is seriously so delicious. I ordered off of uber so I can’t speak about service, but this is honestly some really tasty stuff!!! kimchi fried rice is fantastic, the imperial rolls are amazing and the mango sticky rice is fabulous!! thank you!!! (oh the thai tea is awesome too!)

Nice service but the fried spring rolls were cold and spongy. Reminded me of frozen LaChoy from Albertsons. Other menu items were good, but the nasty rolls somewhat changed our opinion of the entire meal.
Rude people

Great food, great environment, plus our server Stacey was absolutely, hands down the most amazing server I have ever encountered, very nice, very professional, and made it a great experience. Will definitely return.
Yumm so good!! Awesome waitstaff, good food, has a great gluten free selection.
Great service and some of the best sushi in town.

Our first trip here a year ago didn't go good but the owner reached out to us and made things right. We finally came back and had a great experience. The bar drinks were fantastic, the sushi was great. We both had the pad Thai and it was phenomenal....we will be back! Thanks

ordered 3 sushi rolls and an appetizer at 6:45pm...the order wasn't even made until 8:50 (per the delivery guy, not even the postmate delivery driver that i paid a premium for) I only live 13 minutes away, then delivered about 9 pm. Never see my business again!! this is what $100 gets you!
My husband ordered from uber eat and was very disappointed the sushi has no meat on it and the boba tea doesn’t even have any back pearl. It was not worth the price

Ordered curbside and waited like 15 minutes tried to call and was immediately hung up on unfortunately. Noodles were overcooked. The duck and lamb shank was delicious. Sushi roll was okay. Fried rice was excellent.

I really enjoyed this place. The music was nice, the food was great and there was a lot of food on the plate for the cost. The lighting is a bit darker which works for me because I don't like bright lights. This will definitely be my monthly Thai restaurant.
Great variety of vegan options. Service exceptional
Vegan sushi! So many vegan options!

Modern vibe yet dated, unassuming and unexciting service, expensive, still one of the best Thai food in town. Pandemic management was questionable: Every other table was kept empty, but we sat less than 4 ft from another group, although the whole back was empty.
Fantastic as usual

I have dined here twice, both times I found the food to be quite underwhelming. The second time I came with a party of 5, one diner thoroughly enjoyed his meal. The rest did not. For the high prices, you're better of getting a table at one of the other restaurants in the area.
Great food and delicious food!!
They have pretty good food.  But their drinks are a little to earthy.
DELICIOUS GREEN CURRY, GREAT Vegan options, FANTASTIC atmosphere, polite staff, exquisite food presentation... This is my go-to place for Thai food.

I like the old menu better but the presentation was as lovely as usual. We had the Tom Kah Gai and the Tom Yum. My friend had the duck and liked it. We also had the strawberry, marionberry sorbet, which was really good. We come here often and I usually get the lunch buffet which is always great! The service is always outstanding. We will be back!

Decent quality of food for the price, there is a bit of lack of attention to detail that detracted from the experience - dust and cobwebs, a trifle shabby in the shadows. The brisket special was dry, but the other food items were exceptional.

This place is a vegan paradise!! Worth every penny for the vegan fare. We have ordered the same dishes for take out once a week for 9 months and credit Mai Thai with helping us to find some joy in this hard year. Thank you for being a bright spot in a hard period of time, thank you for always being delicious, and thank you for helping us stay plant-based!! Cheers to 2021!
Told me my food would be ready at 6:15. Got it at 7. Last time I’m tipping ahead of time.

We have had issues with the service at Mai Thai in the past but we love the food. We recently had family in town and decided to give it another chance. I’m glad we did! Our family was very impressed to say the least. The service was excellent this time, I think our servers name was Amanda? She took such great care of our table, she was funny, fast and very charming. We will definitely be coming. Thanks for the great night!
Our waiter was UBER wonderful.
Merry Xmass. Thank you.
The amount of plastic used in their to-go is extreme. Each individual lime in a non-recyclable plastic tub. Avoid to-go from them for the planets sake. Love the food though!

Really good food but bartender needs a serious attitude check. Went in to pick up my order and he  even say hello. Had to awkwardly approach and when I said hello he seemed very annoyed. I don't know if this is a one off thing but it made me feel very unwelcome. Doesn't make me feel good about coming back either. Food is super good though, but even that can't make up for rude customer service.
Good place for Thai
Food was ok.   Service was very friendly and the space is nice.

Ordered Lunch from here today.  Not only was it delivered on time, it was hot and SUPER delicious.  I will eat this for 3 meals.  It was a LOT of food and the spice was SPOT on!!!  Great Thai! I will order from here again!

Great Thai food! Third time here and we brought some out of towners in to give it a try. Had three appetizers, an entree each, and shared some mango sticky rice. We had boba and hot tea and some of the custom mixed drinks. (The tea cup was SO COOL) Everything was great, definitely plan on going again! The pad se ew is my personal favourite, and there's always so much food I've got leftovers for days. Good food, good price, good service.  Great place!
Worst takeout ever.  Over-cooked chicken, no flavor, no seasoning with the rice.  A charade.  I'm never this harsh, but wow- subpar on every level.
Great food at atmosphere

Absolutely wonderful. The sushi rolls were perfect and Tom Ka Gai was delicious with flavors spot on, and came in a flaming soup kettle so we could finish it hot. Large drink menu with lots of specialties and fun presentation. Our server was awesome, very knowledgeable and attentive but not overbearing. Great part of Boise, I didn't mind parking a few blocks away and walking past surrounding cute shops and lively patios to get there. Will definitely be back to try more of the menu.

We got curry, sushi, and spring rolls. The spring rolls were good, the sushi tasted weird, and the curry had little pieces of hard plastic in it. So I guess if you don't mind consuming plastic, go for it.

First time here after getting a recommendation from a friend. Quite surprising to see all the bad reviews after eating here because I was nothing but impressed. The food was all fantastic, presentation beautiful. Cocktails were wonderful and the pricing was very reasonable. Our service was very good, another couple did walk out after being served waters but I couldn’t tell why. Based off this experience I already want to come back tomorrow.

Horrible experience with this restaurant. Asked host a question about wait time and was yelled at. She really needs to lay off with the sharpie on her eyebrows. Bad customer service, please get some staff that treats customers with respect.
With a drink that will live on in the pantheon of favorite mixed drinks and memorably good food, my only issue is that I don’t have one of these near my.  Simply wonderful.
Over priced, greasy, lacks flavor. Stingy on their sushi roles

Ordered food 2 hours prior to its delivery time and it still came 50 minutes late. Great food, amazing people, awesome customer service, but the delivery times are not great. Food was still warm, which I appreciated but nonetheless not a great experience with delivery. Please do better, this is not the first time that food has come this late given ample time to make and deliver.
Goodness!  The good was fantastic and the waiter was super attentive. I can't get over how flavorful everything was.  I need to eat here once a week,!

We'll my wife attempted to surprise me with dinner, since our schedules were cramped. She decided to order dinner to go. She ordered Tom yum soup with shrimp, pad see you, and yellow curry with brown rice. She indicated that she did not want any carrots in any of the food. When she arrived home, we discovered that the shrimp were not even cooked, our curry had carrots, and soup was more like luke warm shrimp broth that had no vegetables. There was only a couple slices of mushroom, five shrimp, and no other veggies. It was an disappointing dinner since we had to cook ours own shrimp andrand our soups. We had a pleasant dinner experience while we dined in once but, I don't think we'll be back.
Always love Mai Thai for their Vegan Menu. It's one of the best in town. Typically save them for special occasions but stopped in for lunch yesterday and my entire family found something to love.
Amazingly delicious

I used to really love this place. Before Covid I went all the time. I even went to their cocktail dinner they had and everything was amazing. I was completely blown away by the new chef's food. I've gone in a few times in the past month and the quality has taken a huge turn for the worst. Everything I've had recently has been completely bland and made without love. After having a particularly bad meal I asked my server to speak with the chef and she informed me that he hasn't worked there in months. Perhaps this is the problem? If you want good thai food go to sa-wad-dee or thai cuisine.
The Penang curry with brisket is super tasty.
Excellent service, amazing food

To be quite honest... The food here wasn't that stellar. Our waiter didn't get us water refills for some time. And then there was a whole other beast that made the dining experience unappealing: no ac and flies everywhere inside. Most of our time eating was spent swatting multiple flies off our faces and food.  We won't be returning. There are far better dining experiences to be had in Boise.

The Resy booking system accepted my reservation booking and we drove into Boise in anticipation given the great photography of its food. But when I got to the restaurant, IT WAS CLOSED. There was no sign indicating an unforeseen need to close, and the Google listing shows they are opened on Sundays from 5-9:30pm. A moment later, another customer arrived and could not believe Mai Thai was closed because she had successfully placed a pick-up order online. If the manager is reading this, please, at least, have some indication on your entrance of a need to close, and suspend your online reservation and order-taking system. I hope to still sample your cuisine in the future. However, getting to Mai Thai requires a significant drive, and I'd like have confidence you will actually be open upon arrival.

Went there with my friend. Loved the place. We ordered Pot stickers and drunken noodles. The food was so delicious and smelt really yummy. The staffs are very friendly and polite. The environment is nice. The price is reasonable.  My only complaint is there is not much parking near the restaurant and it is a very busy restaurant and you have to wait to have a seat. It is better to have reservation before going there.  But still I highly recommend this place.
Great food, and the staff was very accommodating our food allergies. Very friendly hostess /waitress
Ordering online and picking up was super easy and convenient, and they had a lot of great vegan options on the menu which was nice! We got the Veggie Green Curry and it was AMAZING! 🙌🏻😋
Great menu items. Gerat customer service. Thanks Mai Thai.

I really wanted to love this place. They have a whole section of their menu dedicated to vegan options which sounded like a dream come true to me even if the food is a bit pricey. I have had vegan honey duck, vegan pad thai, vegan drunken noodles, vegan potstickers, crispy spring rolls, summer rolls, and even attended a fundraiser for a local animal sanctuary here that had a vegan buffet. The flavors of the food isjis off. A lot of the food I've tried was sour or just weird flavor combinations that don't work. Portions are small for the price. When I ordered the vegan drunken noodles it came out with what looked like eggs. I told the server that it was supposed to be vegan. He assured me it was so I had him ask the kitchen staff who owned up to the mistake. When I asked what verisoy was he said that my dish would come with more vegetables, I later learned it's their mock meat. After spending hundreds of dollars here hoping to find something I enjoyed I think I'm done coming here. I'm not new to eating Thai food. Had a place I frequented regularly before moving to the Treasure Valley.
Wait times are atrocious for to-go food. They will tell you one hour regardless of how long you'll actually wait. Get your food elsewhere until they can figure out their to-go service.

Food is good but that is if you want to wait over an hour and a half to two hours for it....they have one delivery driver as what they told me and they are always super busy.. if that is true wouldnt they hire more delivery drivers? And if the kitchen is short staff then would you again hire more people? Plenty of good people looking for jobs....

I very rarely leave reviews this bad, but I just ordered Mai Thai on Door Dash, trying their food for the first time in a long long time. I ordered the vegetarian ramen and the vegetarian bao. I can’t even stress enough, I may as well have been eating cardboard. Neither item had any flavor whatsoever. It was the most bizarre thing I’ve ever experienced from restaurant food. I tried adding sriacha to the ramen, now I could taste heat, but nothing else. So I added a packet of soy sauce. Still nothing. So I added some hoisin (should have just ordered pho elsewhere apparently) and seriously nothing. And no, I don’t have COVID, haha. Keep in mind this is $13 ramen! Definitely just buy the stuff for 59¢ from the grocery store. The dumplings only flavor was a slight bitterness from whatever was mushed inside. I dipped those in leftover orange sauce from another restaurant which helped, but only because it then tasted like orange sauce. I’d skip Mai Thai and go with a place that serves food with flavor. Sorry Mai Thai, but very very bad. I swear, I think the cook forgot to use whatever spices and seasonings they were supposed to and served me pure flour and water.
I don’t usually write reviews but we tried this place due to the high rating and the food was horrible! Just no flavor and the sushi tasted like garbage.

I know it's all weird times lately with the pandemic, but this place has had 5 months to figure it out and get their system down.  Last week I ordered pick-up by phone, the hostess said 30 mins and it took 2 HOURS before my meal was ready for pick-up. No offers of apology or anything, I thought that must of been a fluke so I ordered pick-up again last night and it took 1.5 hrs before my meal was ready. Unacceptable, this place needs to figure it out.
Curry was good, the pad Thai was full of good flavors 🤩

I keep wanting to like this place but it makes it hard when they disappoint me every time. The food is overpriced for the quality and the staff are unfriendly and usually not very professional. The only good thing is their buffet lunch. There are much better Thai places around and I will be taking my business elsewhere from now on.
Delicious food. Fantastic service. Door Dash delivered the incorrect order and Mai Thai remade my correct order and got it delivered.

Ordered doordash from this restaurant. Hot mama roll. When it arrived it smelt werid sort of like cat food, so I inspected the food. Then I seen a little white stick come out of my sushi. So I decided to pull it out. 1 alive moving worm. I had recorded it on my Instagram page to keep my friends aware of this incident. So I decided to ripped the sushi open, so far I've found 5. 3 alive and 2 who stop moving after a while. I am definitely  not satisfied. One of my photos have been deleted by this company. I have posted the ones with worms in there photo tab.

Great Food, Horrible Service  Mai Thai’s food is actually very tasty (hence the two stars), which is unfortunate as I’ve almost never had a good experience there, whether it’s picking up for myself, or for a delivery service. The major issue is the wait times, as food is regularly late for one reason or another. Recently, I had to wait for almost 35 minutes past the ETA listed on my online ticket and received no explanation from the staff. Keep in mind that I had submitted the online order nearly an hour prior to the stated pick-up time that they estimated.  I understand that there can be delays as I also work as a food delivery driver and usually I side with the businesses in cases like these, but when this issue repeats itself on multiple occasions, there’s obviously a problem. There’s also issue for delivery drivers too, as on multiple occasions, the food hasn’t been ready when I arrived at the restaurant at or after the delivery time stated. I’ve talked to other delivery drivers on occasion while waiting and they seem to have the same problem.  There also seems to sometimes be an issue with quality control, as sometimes the food is great and other times it’s not so good. In my most recent (and most likely final) order, the spring rolls were quite dry and “old-tasting”, while the curry was perfectly fine. This isn’t their primary issue, but it’s worth being stated nonetheless.  TL:DR - Mai Thai has decently good food, as long as you’re willing to take the chance on having to wait an excessively long time for it. I personally won’t be accepting delivery orders or making a personal one from them again.
Great service and yummy food! Plus, lots of vegan options.
GREAT BARTENDER GREAT ATMOSPHERE...ONLY PROBLEM I HAVE  IS THE IS AN ODOR THAT MAKES IT VERY UNAPPETIZING
A bit pricey and serving to a niche market. What I had was pretty good, but my dining companion did not enjoy their dish.
Yellow veg curry! Yum.

Fifty minutes after our scheduled pick up order was supposed to be ready it’s still not ready. The  server told me that they had to take care of walk in customers. What!?! If this was the first time that service was chaotic, careless and indifferent I would overlook it. However, this was the case three times in a row. The first two times, items were missing from the order as well. This time when we asked to check the order we were told, “I’m not going to open the bags.” If I owned this place I would want to know how badly my staff and kitchen were performing.

I got some pad thai from your place and it was like eating dried up mush. Even the chicken was dried out. So disappointed. If I could get my money back that would be awsome. Cause I couldn't eat it it was that bad

On behalf of a close friend, I am writing this review. My dear friend worked here within the past two years. I do not write this review based on personal experience, but based on my friends experience. Their experience was not a good one. And there are many others that have had similar difficulties with this restaurant. While Mai Thai can be highly praised for its food and beverages, that is about all it can be praised for. My friend spoke of working at Mai Thai as being emotionally draining. Team members are often yelled at and verbally abused. Being called “stupid” and having their jobs and pay threatened. For employees, Mai Thai is a very high stress environment. The management cares about money more than anything, including the health of its employees and safety of its customers.
Told me my order would be done in few minutes! I still here 30  minutes later! It not a time consuming order! Less yack yack more complete your work(

I usually do not spend the time to write these, I made a to go order at 3:25pm for delivery at 5:15pm knowing the restaurant did not reopen for dinner until 5pm. I specifically made the online to go order well in advance due to a delivery earlier in the week from this same Mai Thai location that took over an hour and a half to deliver. I ordered my first order at 6:30pm and did not receive my food from that order until 8pm. Destined to not make that same mistake I pre ordered my second order online at 3:25pm . I received a call at 5pm with the restaurant stating that the delivery drivers did not get in until 5:30pm however I had been the first order and should receive it shortly after. At 6:30pm an hour and a half after the first initial call I called the restaurant back. They stated again that the delivery drivers got in at 5:30 and that they had a lot of orders. I’m writing this review at now 6:40 and still have not received my order.  LONG STORY SHORT:  expect upwards of 2 hours delivery. At 5:45pm I made an order at The Thai house and received it at 6:15pm.  Note: I spoke with the manager the next day and the issue was resolved.

Ordered online. The ordering system told me 7:15, but they were super busy and it wasn’t ready. They comped my meal, since I had to wait a bit longer. Totally fine with paying regardless, but shows they really care about customers. They are hard workers and very sweet. Food was fantastic as per usual!
I ordered the summer rolls and they gave me a raw shrimp in one of them. I was a little disgusted. The sushi and noodles were good!! But the raw shrimp in the summer roll wasn’t great.

The food tastes great. However, IF YOU HAVE FOOD ALLERGIES, IT IS NOT SAFE TO EAT HERE. The staff does NOT take allergies seriously and frequently makes mistakes. They do not think that mistakes are a big deal. Anyone with food allergies should AVOID this restaurant.  For everyone without food allergies, it's really great and they have an extensive vegan menu.
Ordered through DoorDash, was so excited to try the half duck! The taste was good however the ”half” duck was more like 1/4 of duck. It was like there were missing pieces
Great happy hour
Love that during the quarantine we can have our favorite food delivered! So delicious. ❤️
Very slow service
Best garlic noodles I’ve had in the states!
The seating area smells like urine.  Disgusting.
Awesome spot to grab food when in a hurry. Their service is swift, pricing is reasonable, awesome ambience. Will come visit again

I have been to Mai Thai several times and the last 2 times I have been very unimpressed. Our experience today was the worst. They were out of the beer my husband wanted, they were out of soy paper for sushi so they used rice paper. The sushi roll we did order didn’t even have what the menu said. Super irritating.

Mai Thai restaurant is a favorite of ours.  The food is terrific and service courteous and prompt.  A long-time resident of Boise and having lived and worked in Thailand for ten plus years, I would rate Boise's Mai Thai food as good as, or better than, most of the Thai restaurants we frequented while living in Thailand.  Not a brag, just cold hard facts.  The only Thai restaurants in Thailand as good as Boise's Mai Thai would be those in Thailand serving fresh caught seafood and those would be hard to beat just about anywhere.  Ray Toronjo
Great food! But wait time is long

Our own little taste of the big city in our lil town. Real modern vibes, open spaces, solid cocktails, and a pretty expansive menu. They've got a BOGO happy hour (which is insane these days) on drinks and cheap bites. Skip the Pad Thai and go for the Garlic noodles or the Panang Curry. So good.
The roasted duck and pork belly was a guilty pleasure but worth it. This restaurant offers up lots of great cocktails and food. The decor and atmosphere makes you come back for more.
Phenomenal lamb shank curry!
Delicious bento boxes and an impressive lunch buffet. Super fast service and good prices. Beautiful restaurant.
This place was so neat and the staff was very friendly.
Great food
Great food good drinks
The vegan menu is fantastic and our waitress was amazing
Very good quality Thai kunch buffet ... best time/freshest food is when they open at 11:30.
I took a girlfriend their for her Birthday on their vegan buffet night.... Delicious!!!!! The staff was super knowledgeable & nice. I will definitely return!!
Great food! Nice atmosphere!

If you are in Boise and looking for good food and cocktails, this is an outstanding choice. Separate vegan menu? Yes, and it's on the front page. Great tiki cocktails? Yes, they have that also. Plus warm, friendly service and when the menu says spicy they mean it. Added bonus: they serve food until 10 PM on weeknights.

I've shared on other reviews that I have my favorite Thai restaurants in each part of the Treasure Valley, and this is definitely my favorite downtown spot. It's a really classy place, and while I've expanded to Pad Prik King at other places, I can't keep myself from ordering their Hidden Pad Thai here. It's amazing.  My daughters also have great memories here. I took them to Les Miserablés a few years ago, and we hit this place before the show. Love it! For those who don't like downtown parking, there's a parking garage right across the street. Take the elevator down and walk across, it's that simple.

More in the pricey side but with the quality of food and drink you can definitely tell why. The bar area gets really chilled from the fromt door during colder seasons, but nonetheless it is a great romantic fancy spot
Lunch buffet is amazing!
My husband and I went to the January buffet and for the first time at the restaurant. We loved all the food. The service was amazing. And we went back for dinner and again, amazing.

Seems price has gone up and quality has gone down? Lots of options on lunch buffet - soup, salad, sushi (never had sushi anywhere outside of a sushi restaurant that was any good), white & fried rice, 6 varying main course options including vegetarian options. Pad Thai was dry and sticky. Curry is always tasty!

I was THRILLED to find out that Mai Thai launched a vegan menu with so many great options! We have been in a few times and everything has been absolutely incredible. The service is always great, the atmosphere is nice, and the serving sizes are large. The pad thai with fried tofu is my favorite, but really you can't go wrong. Also, the chickpeas are the best I've ever found in a restaurant.
Their yellow curry is the best I've ever had!
The food here is savory and fresh.  They often use freshly cut basil and sauces.  A little expensive but worth it.  I would recommend the Panang Curry for sit in or uber eats.
A favorite happy hour stop! The food is delicious, and there are vegan options!
Everyone was super kicked back loved helping the customer super tasty food we will definitely be back again highly recommended

AVOID ON WEEKENDS DUE TO SPOILED FISH -- I want to love this place so much, as the location is great, drinks are good, and overall atmosphere is positive. However, I have had several occasions where the fish was outright spoiled on busy nights. My most recent trip being bad enough to prompt this review. I came with my wife on Friday and we ordered 3 drinks, an appetizer and 3 sushi rolls. The drinks and app were great, but the sushi rolls were beyond bad. The fish was spoiled and inedible. We alerted our waiter to this fact and assured him that while our drinks and app were great and we wanted to pay full price, our fish was too rotten to eat. We only had a total of 4 pieces between us two. He said, no worries, and checked in with management. He came back and said, he could only give us a "50% discount because we did eat the majority of our meal.".....we definitely didn't, but this felt like a fair compromise as we knew it wasn't his fault...then we read the bill. It wasn't 50%, but rather 15% off. Couldn't believe it. We paid the requested price and didn't argue, as it wasn't our waiter's fault, but my goodness. How embarrassing out of management. They lost our business for good, no question. I would caution others against this place on weekends, as our experience has been quiet poor. Even on a good night, you're paying for atmosphere and location with the food prices, but when they serve mealy, ruined fish on weekends...hard no, I'll go elsewhere.
Excellent Thai food while visiting my daughter. Nice atmosphere.

The food was way to greasy. I ordered chicken pad Thai. I got maybe 3 pieces of chicken in it. And it was so bad I almost puked after only eating half of it. On top of that the tables and the chairs were sticky and there was a odor in the carpet. You could tell it had not been properly cleaned in a while

The bartender at Mai Thai is amazing! Fantastic, creative drinks. Cool cups too. The food and service was also excellent. I recommend the papaya salad, super fresh, and enough to be a shared appetizer. They've got good vegan options, and our waiter recommended the fried tofu as a protein in the pad se-ew, which was delicious and super flavorful.

Love Mai Thai. They have a great atmosphere and carring staff. The food is always amazing and as a person that eats meat they have the best vegitarian and vegan food I have ever tasted. I like many of the vegan dishes better than the non vegan counter-parts. If you have ever wanted to try vegan but have been afraid to try they do a vegan buffet about once a month. This place is a Boise staple for my family. They never disappoint.
This is a great Asian cuisine restaurant! Great lunch buffet.

Having eaten at the restaurant on numerous occasions, they do a decent job. Mixed drinks are good and the in house sushi is generally good. Conversely, I ordered Uber eats on 3 occasions and they have fulfilled the order, as ordered, zero times. Just bear that in mind when you order via delivery services. The upshot is a free meal. So while they can’t fulfill a delivery, I’m always happy to eat for free.
The vegan menu is super yummy. Ambience is very soothing. Great place to make you feel nice after a long hard day.
Great atmosphere and great American Asian cuisine.
Great atmosphere and an AMAZING vegan menu

My husband works for a company based out of Boise so we tried this gem one time when we were in town. They have the best cashew chicken I have ever tasted, even thinking about it makes my mouth water; I wanted to lick the platter but restrained. The waitress recommended pairing it with the coconut milk rice, it was the perfect combination; I can’t wait to try it again.
Mai Thai has awesome drinks and food. Try and come during happy hour so you can get their buy-one-get-one drink deal!
Very mediocre 🤷🏻‍♀️ again. Thought it might be better, but was definitely not worth the price tag. Sorry!
Good service and yummy food. But take a long time for the food
Ordered via Uber Eats. Order was delivered over an hour late. No help from the restaurant
Drunken noodles were good! Boa Buns under cooked...raw dough. Waiter was friendly maybe new but trying real hard to do a good job.
Was impressed with the food.
Food was OK. Place could be cleaner. Service was slow.
Pretty good food with slow service as others have pointed out.
Yummm food and unbeatable vegan dishes plus cocktails
Great to eat there, but don't order to go, they get it wrong more than half the time...
Good food, great service and not over priced.
Outstanding service and great food. Our sever was knowledgable and helpful.

First of all, some things to note about Mai Thai. The cocktails? Phenomenal. The bartenders? Babes. The happy hour? Best in town. There's a reason Mai Thai has won lots of foodie awards - their menu and offerings are superb.  However, that being said, I had an experience there during a recent happy hour that really ruined it for me. A gentleman -- who I assume was a manager based on how he was dressed -- brought out the food I'd ordered for happy hour. I immediately realized there was a mix up, brought it to his attention, and instead of a typical "Hey no problem, we'll take care of it" kind of response, he berated me in front of the people at my table for the mistake and told me "the food during happy hour is already cheap" so I shouldn't make extra requests. He fought me for an uncomfortably long time in front of a busy restaurant. On top of that, he publicly scolded our wonderful waitress. It was one of the most unprofessional things I've seen in a restaurant and really ruined the experience. I'm bummed that Mai Thai would risk their reputation by keeping someone around who treats their customers and staff that way.

Happy Hour 5/5 Healthy Choices 4/5 (based on happy hour menu only) Bar 5/5 EASY! Seating 3/5 location 5/5 Price 4/5 Overall diversity and comfort level 5/5  Wow! What a good time! I've been wanting to try this place for some time and tonight I finally did! Yay! I'm a SUPER fan and will visit again soon, tomorrow perhaps?!?  Walking in, I was nervous because I didn't have reservations and I looked at other reviews on Yelp using the keyword "Happy hour" and it was very clear that I needed reservations. I walked in about 5 pm and I was the only person there, which allowed me to look around and take some photos. Beautiful-- period. Shortly thereafter the people rolled in, and rolled in, which was an ah ha moment! Get there early! The crowd was all over the place, which as a sociologist I loved. People are beautiful and amaze me! This is a smaller establishment and they do their best with space. Look up at the fans--- never seen that before (look at my video).  Being a single dad of 4 I've recently learned that Happy Hour is a way to get what you want, and pay half the price and Mai Thai didn't disappoint. The waiter was very nice, knowledgeable, and receptive.  Happy Hour is 1/2 price apps and BOGO drinks! You must sit in the bar area for Happy Hour, but there are over 10 tables, one booth and ample seating at the actual bar. You just can't sit in the dining room.  This is what we ordered:  Portobello Tempura Mushrooms ($6 happy hour $12 regular) A++ Huge chunks of Mushroom tempura covered and fried. Served with Sweet Soy sauce. Epic!  California Roll--  ($5 HH $10 reg) These rolls were wrapped very tightly and big chunks with quality ingredients-- another A+ Ordered two of them! Classic Kani and avocado roll with sesame and cucumber.  Thai Chicken Satay's with a peanut sauce ($6 HH $12 reg.) 3/5-- not my favorite, but good nevertheless. _________________________________________________________ ********* DRINKS************ Full bar-- bartenders are true mixologists! Their menu has lots of signature drinks and lots of different expirimental drinks. Again, BOGO. I ordered:  First was Spiced & Iced-- Markers Mark, Averna, Amarula, Thai Chili Honey, Mint, Thai Iced Coffee and vanilla whip. This was really good, but has a little spice to it, which is good-- just beware.  Should I get another? Of course, I should because it's free! BOGO ... I couldn't decide between the house Mai Thai or the or the smoke show. I asked the waiter and he was 100% invested in the smoke show, which is: Bulleit, rye, Benedictine, Peychaud, burnt pineapple, with baked pinecone smoke. When it was brought over you could smell the smokiness... mmmm it was good n strong.  Well, thanks for reading. I hope you get to enjoy Mai Thai and have the most amazing day ever! Thanks for reading!
